/target
# Cargo.lock IS committed: neotop is a binary crate, so locking
# the exact dependency set is what guarantees reproducible CI
# builds (`cargo --locked`) and bisects. The Cargo book recommends
# tracking it for binaries and excluding it only for libraries.
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# Obsidian vault — per-user state and plugin binaries (plugins are
# re-downloaded per machine from the community-plugins list).
# Exception: the two mermaid plugins that make the charts in docs/
# and README.md zoomable / draggable ship with the repo so a fresh
# clone has them out of the box.
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache
.obsidian/plugins/*
!.obsidian/plugins/mermaid-popup/
!.obsidian/plugins/mermaid-tools/
.devin/
